1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,800
I really didn't think I was gonna have a good time, but I did. I totally did.

2
00:00:02,800 --> 00:00:04,000
I love camping.

3
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:05,800
Anything can happen.

4
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:09,000
Aw, it wasn't camping. It was more of a wilderness retreat.

5
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Morning.

6
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:11,000
Michael.

7
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Ryan invited some of the branch managers and Toby into the woods for a get-to-know-you weekend.

8
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
Michael wasn't invited.

9
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Apparently they already knew everything they needed to know about him.

10
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:27,000
I thought it'd be a good idea to have a retreat with some guys that I like, but no one wanted to fund it.

11
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Fix it, Ryan. Find a solution, Ryan.

12
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Fine, guys. Did I mention it's a green retreat?

13
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:37,000
What happens next? Corporate funds your camping trip and all the cute secretaries are like, huh, check it out.

14
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
That new wunderkind guy is kind of a do-gooder.

15
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:44,000
I'll let you in on a little secret. No one ever does anything for the environment just to help the environment.

16
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
If someone tells you they have a green initiative, it's a scam.

17
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Do I feel guilty? Please. I went surfing last weekend. The ocean's still there. Unseasonably warm, actually. It was gorgeous.

18
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Did you sleep in cabins?

19
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Under the stars. It was really beautiful. You should have come.

20
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Bob and I took rock climbing lessons once.

21
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Michael wasn't invited on Ryan's camping trip. Toby went, but Michael didn't go. He wasn't invited.

22
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,000
Who went?

23
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Me, Dan from Buffalo, Mark Chisholm, Jeff from Albany, and Ryan, obviously.

24
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:25,000
We had so many s'mores I finally had to say. No more s'mores. No more s'mores.

25
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Ryan invited me to go on his wilderness adventure retreat. It was this amazing, beautiful experience.

26
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Hey, nobody cares. Nobody cares. I need that room at some point, so just wrap it up.

27
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Michael wasn't invited.

28
00:01:50,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Music

29
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Knock, knock. Come in.

30
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Oh, it's Creed's birthday today. Should we get him an ice cream cake, mint chocolate chip?

31
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Pam, are you my friend?

32
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Oh, no.

33
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:28,000
We have been friends forever, right?

34
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Yes, I have been working with you forever.

35
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Hypothetically, would you go camping with me if I were to ask you? And bear in mind that I would never actually ask you to go camping.

36
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:48,000
The gym is also a friend of mine, and I would rather die than make any sort of improper ovation toward you.

37
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,000
I don't think so.

38
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Here's the thing. When Michael invents a hypothetical situation, he eventually turns it into an actual situation.

39
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Do you understand that Jim is like a brother to me, and I would never do anything inappropriate?

40
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,000
I do.

41
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:07,000
So, as friends, would you go with me on a camping trip?

42
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,000
No.

43
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Thank you for your honesty.

44
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
You're welcome. Open or closed?

45
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Split the difference.

46
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Hey, mint chocolate chip, please? Is Jim out there?

47
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,000
No.

48
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Can you send Dwight in here?

49
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,000
Yeah. Dwight, Michael wants to see you in his office.

50
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,000
You want him to see me?

51
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Mm-hmm. I have something very personal I would like to discuss.

52
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Would you go find Jim and send him in here, please?

53
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,000
I'm on it.

54
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Michael has employed Dwight to track you down.

55
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,000
How much time do we have?

56
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Jim, Michael's office.

57
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,000
A couple minutes, give or take.

58
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Now, Jim.

59
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:56,000
Hypothetically, if I were to ask you to go camping, and you know what hypothetical means, not real.

60
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,000
Got it.

61
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:02,000
So, if I were to hypothetically ask you to go camping with me, would you go?

62
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Absolutely, yes.

63
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,000
When Michael plays the hypothetical game, I always say yes.
